  "bookId": 56,
  "firstAcquaintance": "A rat-kin girl shunned by other demons, she lives a low-profile life in the Shadow District to avoid trouble. She excels at running away. Secretly, she's the Shadow District's mysterious merchant.",
  "personality": "Always appears lazy and carefree, with no grand ambitions. Good at using clever tricks to make life a little easier.",
  "like": "Shoes, money",
  "familiarData": "Gozona inherited guerrilla combat techniques from her mother, a rat-kin soldier. She's an expert in guerrilla warfare, but her laid-back personality means she has no interest in joining the demon army.\nHer inherited combat skills haven't gone to waste. Gozona uses her abilities to earn extra income and live comfortably, though she remains firmly committed to her philosophy of 'no grand ambitions, just living the easy life.' She always knows exactly how to keep a low profile while making money.\nBy day, she works in a kitchen. On the side, she uses her racial talents to scavenge recyclable goods from the dump, repairs them, and resells them for extra income as the Shadow District's mysterious merchant.\nSome repairs require a blacksmith's help, so she sneaks into Yaya's smithy to trade food and candy for assistance. The two actually get along quite well.",
